CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 25, 1961, pg. B5 reads: "More Than 300 Attend Chi Dance - Among the more than 300 guests attending the smart Chi Delta Mu Fraternity supper dance last Saturday evening at the Pittsburgh Hilton was the above group. Seated clockwise at Dr. and Mrs. William Sessions table are: Mr. and Mrs. Robert Woodruff, Dr. and Mrs. J.D. Phillips of Harrisburg, Mrs. Session, Dr. Session, Mrs. Thomas Stokes and Mrs. Stokes.  Mr. and Mrs. Percy A. Garland are missing from the picture..."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, clockwise: Mr. and Mrs. Robert Woodruff, Dr. and Mrs. J.D. Phillips, Mrs. and Dr. Session, and Mrs. and Mr. Thomas Stokes, seated at banquet table in Hilton Hotel for Chi Delta Mu supper dance
